{"parse":{"title":"Francis J. Bradley","pageid":46918626,"revid":761180040,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Francis_J_Bradley-2012.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c4/Francis_J_Bradley-2012.png/220px-Francis_J_Bradley-2012.png\" width=\"220\" height=\"247\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c4/Francis_J_Bradley-2012.png/330px-Francis_J_Bradley-2012.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c4/Francis_J_Bradley-2012.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"390\" data-file-height=\"438\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Francis_J_Bradley-2012.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Francis J. Bradley, American health physicist, writer and founding member of the Health Physics Society</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Francis J. Bradley</b> (born 15 January 1926) is an American health physicist, writer and founding member of the <a href=\"/wiki/Health_Physics_Society\" title=\"Health Physics Society\">Health Physics Society</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Life_and_times\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Life and times</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#AEC_Fellowship\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">AEC Fellowship</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Oak_Ridge_and_Elda_E._Anderson\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Oak Ridge and Elda E. Anderson</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Ohio_State_University\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Ohio State University</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#New_York_State\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">New York State</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Health_Physics_Society\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Health Physics Society</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#First_Board_of_Directors\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">First Board of Directors</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#International_Atomic_Energy_Agency\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">International Atomic Energy Agency</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Project_Long_Shot_and_Vela_Project\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">8</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Project Long Shot and Vela Project</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">9</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Life_and_times\">Life and times</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Francis_J._Bradley&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Life and times\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Francis J. \"Frank\" Bradley was born on 15 January 1926 in <a href=\"/wiki/New_York_City\" title=\"New York City\">New York City</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Queens\" title=\"Queens\">Queens County</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/New_York_(state)\" title=\"New York (state)\">New York</a>. Bradley\u2019s father was a New York City <a href=\"/wiki/Fireman\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fireman\">fireman</a>. The Bradley family lived in <a href=\"/wiki/Corona,_Queens\" title=\"Corona, Queens\">Corona, Queens</a> New York. \nBradley worked his way up to the rank of <a href=\"/wiki/Sergeant\" title=\"Sergeant\">sergeant</a> in the <a href=\"/wiki/U.S._Army_Air_Force\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"U.S. Army Air Force\">U.S. Army Air Force</a> pulling duty as a <a href=\"/wiki/Air_gunner\" title=\"Air gunner\">gunner</a> aboard a <a href=\"/wiki/B-29\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"B-29\">B-29</a> bomber and served in the <a href=\"/wiki/Asiatic-Pacific_Theater\" title=\"Asiatic-Pacific Theater\">Pacific Theater of Operations</a> during <a href=\"/wiki/World_War_II\" title=\"World War II\">World War II</a>. Bradley graduated in 1949 from <a href=\"/wiki/Manhattan_College\" title=\"Manhattan College\">Manhattan College</a> with a degree in <a href=\"/wiki/Electrical_engineering\" title=\"Electrical engineering\">electrical engineering</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Cember_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Cember-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"AEC_Fellowship\">AEC Fellowship</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Francis_J._Bradley&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: AEC Fellowship\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In June 1949 Bradley applied for the <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_Atomic_Energy_Commission\" title=\"United States Atomic Energy Commission\">Atomic Energy Commission</a> (AEC) Fellowship in <a href=\"/wiki/Health_physics\" title=\"Health physics\">Radiological Physics</a> and passed the examination administered at <a href=\"/wiki/Columbia_University\" title=\"Columbia University\">Columbia University</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Cember_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Cember-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> While taking the exam he met <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Herman_Cember&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Herman Cember (page does not exist)\">Herman Cember</a>. Bradley and Cember passed the test but were delayed in starting the Fellowship as they waited for their <a href=\"/wiki/Q_clearance\" title=\"Q clearance\">Q clearance</a> to be completed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Cember_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Cember-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Oak_Ridge_and_Elda_E._Anderson\">Oak Ridge and Elda E. Anderson</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Francis_J._Bradley&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Oak Ridge and Elda E. Anderson\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Bradley began his career in health physics and radiological protection when he received an <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_Atomic_Energy_Commission\" title=\"United States Atomic Energy Commission\">Atomic Energy Commission</a> Fellowship grant in Radiological Physics at <a href=\"/wiki/Oak_Ridge_National_Laboratory\" title=\"Oak Ridge National Laboratory\">Oak Ridge National Laboratory</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Pratt_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Pratt-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> At Oak Ridge he started in the second class of <a href=\"/wiki/Elda_E._Anderson\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Elda E. Anderson\">Elda E. Anderson</a> with students that included: <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Herman_Cember&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Herman Cember (page does not exist)\">Herman Cember</a>, <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Allen_Brodsky&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Allen Brodsky (page does not exist)\">Allen Brodsky</a> and <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Lester_Rogers&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Lester Rogers (page does not exist)\">Lester Rogers</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Ohio_State_University\">Ohio State University</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Francis_J._Bradley&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Ohio State University\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Francis J. Bradley went on to the <a href=\"/wiki/Ohio_State_University\" title=\"Ohio State University\">Ohio State University</a> responsible for Radiation Inspection as the Superintendent of Radiation Safety effective 25 May 1953 with an <a href=\"/wiki/Annual_salary\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Annual salary\">annual salary</a> of $6,324.00.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> While at Ohio State, Bradley became a Fallout Shelter Analysis Instructor at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Pennsylvania\" title=\"University of Pennsylvania\">University of Pennsylvania</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"New_York_State\">New York State</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Francis_J._Bradley&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: New York State\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In 1977 Bradley held the position of Principal Radiophysicist, Division of Safety &amp; Health, New York State Department of Labor.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Bradley spent 20 years with the <a href=\"/wiki/New_York_State\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New York State\">New York State</a> Department of Labor, Radiological Health Unit as the Principle Radiophysicist.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\nBradley was the ANSI N43 Representative for the American Public Health Association in 1985.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Health_Physics_Society\">Health Physics Society</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Francis_J._Bradley&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Health Physics Society\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In 1955 while Superintendent of Radiation Safety at <a href=\"/wiki/Ohio_State_University\" title=\"Ohio State University\">Ohio State University</a> Bradley organized the initial conference of <a href=\"/wiki/Health_physicist\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Health physicist\">health physicists</a> and from this meeting the <a href=\"/wiki/Health_Physics_Society\" title=\"Health Physics Society\">Health Physics Society</a> was formed with <a href=\"/wiki/Karl_Z._Morgan\" title=\"Karl Z. Morgan\">Karl Z. Morgan</a> as President, <a href=\"/wiki/Frederick_P._Cowan\" title=\"Frederick P. Cowan\">Frederick P. Cowan</a> as Vice President, and <a href=\"/wiki/Elda_E._Anderson\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Elda E. Anderson\">Elda E. Anderson</a> as Secretary/Treasurer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\nIn the midyear issue of <a href=\"/wiki/Science\" title=\"Science\">Science</a> the announcement came of the formation new national scientific organization for health physicists at the 3 day Health Physics Conference at Ohio State University in Columbus, Ohio on 14 June 1955.<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ul><li>Founding member and Director</li>\n<li>Charter member</li>\n<li>Life member</li>\n<li>Founders Award, 1988<sup id=\"cite_ref-Cember_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Cember-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>President, Government Section, 2000</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Gioacchino_Failla#Failla_Memorial_Lecture\" title=\"Gioacchino Failla\">Failla Memorial Award</a>, 23 January 2001<sup id=\"cite_ref-Pratt_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Pratt-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<p>In the midyear issue of <a href=\"/wiki/Science_(journal)\" title=\"Science (journal)\">Science</a> the announcement came of the formation new national scientific organization for health physicists at the 3 day Health Physics Conference at Ohio State University in Columbus, Ohio on 14 June 1955.<sup id=\"cite_ref-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup> The organization was temporarily named \"Health Physics Society\", and <a href=\"/wiki/Karl_Z._Morgan\" title=\"Karl Z. Morgan\">Karl Z. Morgan</a> of the Health Physics Division of Oak Ridge National Laboratory was elected interim president. Other interim officers are: \n</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Frederick_P._Cowan\" title=\"Frederick P. Cowan\">Frederick P. Cowan</a>, Head, Health Physics Division <a href=\"/wiki/Brookhaven_National_Laboratory\" title=\"Brookhaven National Laboratory\">Brookhaven National Laboratory</a>, Upton, N.Y., vice president, and</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Elda_E._Anderson\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Elda E. Anderson\">Elda E. Anderson</a>, director of the education and training department of the Health Physics Division, <a href=\"/wiki/Oak_Ridge_National_Laboratory\" title=\"Oak Ridge National Laboratory\">Oak Ridge National Laboratory</a>, secretary-treasurer.</li></ul>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"First_Board_of_Directors\">First Board of Directors</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Francis_J._Bradley&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: First Board of Directors\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Talks regarding the formation of a professional society had been ongoing for several years. The health physicists had decided to form an independent organization rather than attach to an existing group.<br />\nDirectors of the Health Physics Society included: \n</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Herbert_Mermagen\" title=\"Herbert Mermagen\">Herbert Mermagen</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Rochester\" title=\"University of Rochester\">University of Rochester</a>, Rochester, N.Y.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Edgar_Charles_Barnes\" title=\"Edgar Charles Barnes\">Edgar Charles Barnes</a>, manager of <a href=\"/wiki/Industrial_hygiene\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Industrial hygiene\">industrial hygiene</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Westinghouse_Atomic_Power_Division\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Westinghouse Atomic Power Division\">Westinghouse Atomic Power Division</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Bettis_Atomic_Power_Laboratory\" title=\"Bettis Atomic Power Laboratory\">Bettis Field</a>, Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania</li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_W._%27Jack%27_Healy&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"John W. &#39;Jack&#39; Healy (page does not exist)\">John W. 'Jack' Healy</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/General_Electric_Co.\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"General Electric Co.\">General Electric Co.</a>, Hanford, Washington</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/William_Taylor_Ham\" title=\"William Taylor Ham\">William Taylor Ham</a>, professor of biophysics, <a href=\"/wiki/Medical_College_of_Virginia\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Medical College of Virginia\">Medical College of Virginia</a>, Richmond, Virginia</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/C._Maurice_Patterson\" title=\"C. Maurice Patterson\">C. Maurice Patterson</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/DuPont#Second_World_War:_1941_to_1945\" title=\"DuPont\">DuPont Atomic Energy Plant</a>, Aiken, S.C.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/G._W._C._Tait\" title=\"G. W. C. Tait\">G. W. C. Tait</a>, Health Physics Branch, <a href=\"/wiki/Atomic_Energy_of_Canada_Limited\" title=\"Atomic Energy of Canada Limited\">Atomic Energy Co. of Canada</a>, Ltd., Chalk River, Ontario, Canada</li>\n<li>Francis J. Bradley, superintendent of radiation safety at <a href=\"/wiki/Ohio_State_University\" title=\"Ohio State University\">Ohio State University</a> and organizer of the first <a href=\"/wiki/Health_Physics_Society\" title=\"Health Physics Society\">Health Physics Society</a> Conference</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Health_Physics_Society#William_Edward_Nolan\" title=\"Health Physics Society\">William E. Nolan</a>, Radiation Laboratory, <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_California,_Berkeley\" title=\"University of California, Berkeley\">University of California, Berkeley</a>, California</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Walter_Dunhan_Claus\" title=\"Walter Dunhan Claus\">Walter Dunhan Claus</a>, (annual salary $12,000), Division of Biology and Medicine, Biophysics Branch, <a href=\"/wiki/U.S._Atomic_Energy_Commission\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"U.S. Atomic Energy Commission\">U.S. Atomic Energy Commission</a>, Washington, D.C.<sup id=\"cite_ref-15\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/John_E._Pickering\" title=\"John E. Pickering\">John E. Pickering</a>, department of <a href=\"/wiki/Radiobiology\" title=\"Radiobiology\">radiobiology</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Randolph_Air_Force_Base#School_of_Aviation_Medicine\" title=\"Randolph Air Force Base\">School of Aviation Medicine</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Randolph_Air_Force_Base\" title=\"Randolph Air Force Base\">Randolph Air Force Base</a>, Texas</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"International_Atomic_Energy_Agency\">International Atomic Energy Agency</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Francis_J._Bradley&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: International Atomic Energy Agency\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Francis_J_Bradley_1961.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Francis_J_Bradley_1961.png/220px-Francis_J_Bradley_1961.png\" width=\"220\" height=\"139\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Francis_J_Bradley_1961.png/330px-Francis_J_Bradley_1961.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Francis_J_Bradley_1961.png/440px-Francis_J_Bradley_1961.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"695\" data-file-height=\"440\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Francis_J_Bradley_1961.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Turkey 1961. Bradley assisted with the establishment of a national radiation control program for the 1 MW nuclear reactor at \u00c7ekmece Nuclear Research and Training Center that went critical on 27 May 1962.</div></div></div>\n<p>In 1961 Bradley worked for the <a href=\"/wiki/International_Atomic_Energy_Agency\" title=\"International Atomic Energy Agency\">International Atomic Energy Agency</a> and went to <a href=\"/wiki/Turkey\" title=\"Turkey\">Turkey</a> and assisted with the establishment of a national radiation control program for the 1 MW <a href=\"/wiki/Nuclear_reactor\" title=\"Nuclear reactor\">nuclear reactor</a> at <a href=\"/wiki/%C3%87NAEM\" title=\"\u00c7NAEM\">\u00c7ekmece Nuclear Research and Training Center</a> that went critical on 27 May 1962. Bradley next went to <a href=\"/wiki/Taiwan\" title=\"Taiwan\">Taiwan</a> to help develop the radiation safety program for the country\u2019s first reactor.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Project_Long_Shot_and_Vela_Project\">Project Long Shot and Vela Project</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Francis_J._Bradley&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: Project Long Shot and Vela Project\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Bradley was involved with <a href=\"/wiki/Amchitka#Long_Shot_test\" title=\"Amchitka\">Project Long Shot</a>, the underground nuclear tests on <a href=\"/wiki/Amchitka_Island\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Amchitka Island\">Amchitka Island</a> that is part of the <a href=\"/wiki/Aleutian_Islands\" title=\"Aleutian Islands\">Aleutian Islands</a>. In 1965 as part of <a href=\"/wiki/Project_Vela\" title=\"Project Vela\">Vela Project</a> he conducted radiological measurements and performed environmental sampling.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Cember_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Cember-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Francis_J._Bradley&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Cember-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Cember_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Cember_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Cember_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Cember_1-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Cember_1-4\"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Cember, H. (June 1989) 1988 Founders Award presented to Francis J. Bradley. Health Physics. 56(6): 811-2.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Pratt-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Pratt_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Pratt_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Pratt, Rose Marie. (June 2001). Frank Bradley is Thirty-Eighth Failla Memorial Award Lecturer, Greater New York Chapter, HPS Newsletter. XXIX(6): 14.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Sicherman, Barbara, and Carol Hurd Green (1980). Notable American Women: The Modern Period. Harvard University Press.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://trustees.osu.edu/assets/files/minutes/Archive%20minutes/1953-1956.pdf\">http://trustees.osu.edu/assets/files/minutes/Archive%20minutes/1953-1956.pdf</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Ryan, Michael T. and Poston, Sr., John W. (2006). A Half Century of Health Physics: 50th Anniversary of the Health Physics Society. Lippincott Williams &amp; Wilkins.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.jumpjet.info/Emergency-Preparedness/Emergency-Shelters/Radiation-Shelter/Architect_&amp;_Engineering_Activities_in_Shelter_Development.pdf\">http://www.jumpjet.info/Emergency-Preparedness/Emergency-Shelters/Radiation-Shelter/Architect_&amp;_Engineering_Activities_in_Shelter_Development.pdf</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span